column2: Police are investigating after the body of a woman was found on a popular Sydney beach early Wednesday morning. A member of the public called emergency services after spotting the body washed up on the northern end of Bronte Beach in the city’s east. “Officers from eastern suburbs police area command were called to the northern end of Bronte Beach after a member of the public found the body about 5.45am today,” a New South Wales police spokesperson said. “A crime scene has been established and inquiries are under way.” Sign up to receive an email with the top stories from Guardian Australia every morning A blue tent has been placed over the body and Waverley council said the beach has been closed until further notice. More to come.
column4: Body of woman found washed up on Sydney’s Bronte Beach
